# Core Philosophy
- Write modular, testable, and highly performant code.
- Prioritize security best practices (input validation, sanitization, secure handling of secrets).
- Stick to standard design patterns (Dependency Injection, Single Responsibility Principle).

# Structural Preferences
- Keep functions small, focused, and pure where possible.
- Avoid deep nesting; use guard clauses to handle edge cases early.
- Docker & CI/CD: Ensure configurations are optimized for fast builds and minimal image sizes.